Create an HTML file with two input fields, a button, and a div element.

Link the HTML file to a JavaScript file using a script tag.

Define a checkCredentials() function in the JavaScript file.

Get the username and password input values using document.getElementById().value.

Check if the input values match "Username" and "Password" using an if statement.

If the values match, set the div element's text content to "Success" using document.getElementById().innerHTML.

If the values do not match, set the div element's text content to "Wrong information".

Test the application by entering "Username" and "Password" into the input fields and clicking the button to see the result in the div element.